table:table-cell.text:p: Note: TSR Tip speed ratio Depends on how much

text:p.text:span: wind the turbine catches and transforms into kinetic
Energy/impulse, i.e.speed via 1/2 m * speed ^2 (energy) or m * v (impulse).

While not all energy can be caught (and shouldn't to get the wind out of the way of new wind influx) the turbine can still rotate quicker (5x for horizontal), depending on pitch angle of turbine blades..

Because despite drag contributions, there still are some losses due to the resistance of the second part. Worst case is 0.5.
